custom_fields.key_topics:
Through readings, discussion, and assignments the course will enable students to:
	understand the roles of society, political institutions and regulatory agencies, non-governmental organizations (NGOs), scientific information, economics and business, and technology on developing energy policies;
	grasp the interplay of scientific, political, and economic factors in the formation of energy policy in the United States at various levels;
	comprehend the interactions of legislative and regulatory frameworks in shaping energy policy; and,
	develop an understanding of set of tools used to judge the need, the sufficiency of, and the effectiveness of energy policy.
